Summary Report: “FCAJ Community Day” Event Objectives Share practical knowledge about modern software development and AWS technologies. Introduce AI-driven development tools and enterprise solutions. Provide career guidance and industry experience from experienced speakers. Encourage continuous learning and collaboration within the developer community. Speakers The workshop featured several experienced speakers from the AWS and software development community.
Master Hưng
Topic: &ldquo;Three Essential Elements for Modern Developers&rdquo;
Highlighted the importance of strong technical foundations. Emphasized continuous learning and practical working experience. Encouraged developers to focus on mastering fundamentals before building products. Tịnh
Topic: &ldquo;Why AI Fails Without Context&rdquo;
Explained the importance of providing sufficient context when using AI. Introduced concepts such as AI-first thinking, prompt engineering, and memory. Shared common mistakes that reduce AI performance. Anh Phạm
Topic: &ldquo;Amazon Q Overview and Demo&rdquo;
Introduced the capabilities of Amazon Q. Demonstrated how Amazon Q assists software development. Shared practical examples of integrating Amazon Q with AWS services. Thịnh
Topic: &ldquo;CloudFront Fixed Pricing and Advanced Security&rdquo;
Explained CloudFront pricing models and cost optimization strategies. Introduced security features including DDoS protection, HTTPS compression, Signed URLs, and VPC Origin. Demonstrated how CloudFront supports scalable and secure applications. UTMorphos Team
Topic: &ldquo;36 Hours with LotusHacks Hackathon&rdquo;
Shared experiences from participating in the LotusHacks hackathon. Presented an AI-powered website template generation tool. Demonstrated how AI simplifies web design and development. Vy Lam
Topic: &ldquo;Enterprise Grade Multi-Agent Systems&rdquo;
Introduced enterprise multi-agent AI architectures. Shared implementation strategies and practical experiences. Explained real-world applications of AI agents in enterprise systems. Key Highlights 1. &ldquo;Three Essential Elements for Modern Developers&rdquo; – Presented by Master Hưng Understood the importance of building strong programming fundamentals. Learned that continuous learning and practical experience are essential for long-term career growth. Realized that developing solid skills should come before focusing on products. 2. &ldquo;Why AI Fails Without Context&rdquo; – Presented by Tịnh Learned that context is a critical factor in achieving high-quality AI responses. Understood how prompts, context, and memory work together in AI systems. Identified common mistakes when interacting with AI tools. 3. &ldquo;Amazon Q Overview and Demo&rdquo; – Presented by Anh Phạm Became familiar with Amazon Q and its AI-assisted development features. Observed real-world demonstrations of Amazon Q in software development. Learned how Amazon Q integrates with AWS services to improve productivity. 4. &ldquo;CloudFront Fixed Pricing and Advanced Security&rdquo; – Presented by Thịnh Learned how CloudFront pricing works and how fixed pricing simplifies cost management. Understood the purpose of advanced security features such as DDoS protection and Signed URLs. Gained a better understanding of CloudFront architecture and CDN optimization. 5. &ldquo;36 Hours with LotusHacks Hackathon&rdquo; – Presented by UTMorphos Team Learned about the challenges and experiences of participating in a hackathon. Understood how AI can automate website template generation from images. Recognized the importance of teamwork and rapid problem-solving during software development. 6. &ldquo;Enterprise Grade Multi-Agent Systems&rdquo; – Presented by Vy Lam Learned the basic architecture of enterprise multi-agent systems. Understood how AI agents collaborate to solve complex business problems. Gained insight into future trends in enterprise AI development. Impact on My Internship Improved my understanding of AI-assisted software development. Gained practical knowledge of CloudFront, Amazon Q, and enterprise AI technologies. Strengthened my awareness of the importance of technical foundations and continuous learning. Community Engagement Connected with AWS community members and experienced developers. Exchanged ideas with students, interns, and software engineers. Expanded my professional network through technical discussions. Future Improvement Plan Continue strengthening programming fundamentals and problem-solving skills. Apply AI context management techniques when using AI development tools. Explore Amazon Q and CloudFront through hands-on practice. Participate in hackathons and technical communities to gain more practical experience. Learn more about enterprise AI and multi-agent system architectures.

Summary Report: “AWS Study Group Workshop - AI in Development Lifecycle” Event Objectives Share practical experiences in organizing and conducting AWS technical workshops. Introduce AWS technologies and best practices used in real-world projects. Demonstrate how AI tools can support different stages of the software development lifecycle. Provide career guidance and professional development advice for students and junior developers. Encourage networking and knowledge sharing within the AWS Study Group community. Speakers The workshop included presentations from experienced members of the AWS Study Group community:
Anh Long (Admin)
Topic: &ldquo;How to Get Addicted to Learning Like Social Media&rdquo;
Introduced practical methods for building long-term learning habits. Explained how to stay motivated and make continuous learning more enjoyable. Anh Thịnh (Admin)
Topic: &ldquo;Automated Prompt Engineering: Enhancing LLM Output Quality&rdquo;
Explained techniques for designing more effective prompts. Demonstrated ways to improve the quality and consistency of AI-generated responses. Anh Khang (Admin)
Topic: &ldquo;Why You Haven’t Started Working Yet&rdquo;
Discussed common obstacles faced by new graduates and job seekers. Shared advice on preparing for a professional career in the technology industry. Guest Speaker (Software Developer)
Topic: &ldquo;BMAD&rdquo; (Build, Measure, Analyze, Deploy)
Introduced the BMAD development workflow. Explained how continuous measurement and analysis contribute to software improvement. Key Highlights 1. &ldquo;How to Get Addicted to Learning Like Social Media&rdquo; – Presented by Anh Long (Admin) Learned how to build consistent learning habits through small daily goals. Understood that discipline is more important than temporary motivation. Gained ideas for improving my personal study routine. 2. &ldquo;Automated Prompt Engineering: Enhancing LLM Output Quality&rdquo; – Presented by Anh Thịnh (Admin) Learned the fundamentals of prompt engineering for large language models. Understood how well-structured prompts improve AI-generated results. Discovered practical ways to use AI tools more effectively during development. 3. &ldquo;Why You Haven’t Started Working Yet&rdquo; – Presented by Anh Khang (Admin) Understood the gap between academic learning and industry requirements. Learned the importance of practical experience, communication, and continuous learning. Identified the skills and mindset needed for career readiness. 4. &ldquo;BMAD (Build, Measure, Analyze, Deploy)&rdquo; – Presented by a Software Developer Learned the basic workflow of the BMAD development methodology. Understood the importance of measuring and analyzing software performance. Recognized the value of continuous improvement throughout development. Impact on My Internship Applied new learning strategies to improve my daily internship routine. Better understood how AI tools such as Kiro can support software development. Realized the importance of combining technical knowledge with professional skills. Community Engagement Connected with AWS Study Group admins and community members. Met other interns and AWS learners with similar interests. Shared experiences and discussed future learning opportunities. Future Improvement Plan Maintain a consistent daily learning schedule. Practice prompt engineering with AI development tools. Build more practical projects to strengthen technical skills. Apply the BMAD methodology in future projects. Continue participating in AWS Study Group activities.

Summary Report: “FCAJ Community Day - AI Agents &amp; DevOps Workshop” Event Objectives Explore the latest AI technologies, cloud solutions, and DevOps practices. Learn from industry experts through technical presentations and live demonstrations. Discover practical applications of AI in software development and enterprise environments. Strengthen technical knowledge while expanding professional connections within the AWS community. Speakers The event featured presentations from experienced professionals, founders, and AWS community members.
Steve Tran (Founder of CloudThinker.io)
Topic: &ldquo;AgenticOps for Your Cloud&rdquo;
Shared his journey from beginner to cloud entrepreneur. Introduced AgenticOps concepts and microservices architecture. Explained when to choose single-agent or multi-agent systems. Nghi Danh, Kiet Tran &amp; Trung Vũ (Founder &amp; CEO of Revve AI)
Topic: &ldquo;Building Voice Agent at Scale&rdquo;
Introduced opportunities in the Voice AI industry. Demonstrated how voice agents are designed and deployed. Discussed common challenges and practical solutions for Voice AI systems. Nguyen Nguyen &amp; Chị Bảo
Topic: &ldquo;AWS DevOps Agent&rdquo;
Introduced AWS DevOps Agent and its core capabilities. Explained AI-powered DevOps automation and AWS integration. Demonstrated deployment automation and infrastructure management. Trường &amp; Chị Anh
Topic: &ldquo;AI-Powered Productivity with Amazon Q&rdquo;
Demonstrated Amazon Q features and real-world business applications. Showed how Amazon Q improves productivity in HR and daily operations. Shared practical implementation experiences. Anh Toàn &amp; Anh Nghi
Topic: &ldquo;Building Secure Private MCP for Amazon Q&rdquo;
Introduced the Model Context Protocol (MCP). Demonstrated secure Amazon Q integration with private enterprise data. Explained VPC-based architecture for secure AI applications. Key Highlights 1. &ldquo;AgenticOps for Your Cloud&rdquo; – Presented by Steve Tran Learned the fundamentals of AgenticOps and cloud automation. Understood the differences between single-agent and multi-agent architectures. Recognized the importance of selecting the right architecture based on project complexity. 2. &ldquo;Building Voice Agent at Scale&rdquo; – Presented by Nghi Danh, Kiet Tran &amp; Trung Vũ Learned how modern Voice AI systems are designed and implemented. Understood the opportunities and limitations of voice-based applications. Gained practical knowledge about improving voice recognition and user experience. 3. &ldquo;AWS DevOps Agent&rdquo; – Presented by Nguyen Nguyen &amp; Chị Bảo Learned how AWS DevOps Agent automates deployment and infrastructure management. Understood the advantages of AI-powered DevOps workflows. Explored practical approaches to improving development efficiency. 4. &ldquo;AI-Powered Productivity with Amazon Q&rdquo; – Presented by Trường &amp; Chị Anh Discovered how Amazon Q can improve productivity across different business functions. Learned practical use cases for HR automation, document management, and data analysis. Understood the benefits of integrating AI into everyday workflows. 5. &ldquo;Building Secure Private MCP for Amazon Q&rdquo; – Presented by Anh Toàn &amp; Anh Nghi Learned the purpose and architecture of the Model Context Protocol (MCP). Understood how Amazon Q securely connects to private enterprise resources. Gained knowledge of VPC-based security and enterprise AI best practices. Impact on My Internship Expanded my understanding of AI agents, Voice AI, and DevOps automation. Learned practical AWS solutions that can be applied to future cloud projects. Improved my awareness of secure AI deployment in enterprise environments. Community Engagement Connected with AWS experts, founders, and software engineers. Exchanged ideas with other students and community members. Expanded my professional network through technical discussions and networking activities. Future Improvement Plan Learn more about AgenticOps and multi-agent architectures. Build small Voice AI and Amazon Q practice projects. Improve my AWS DevOps knowledge through hands-on experience. Continue studying enterprise AI security and MCP architecture. Participate in more AWS community events and technical workshops.
